window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>“It isn’t easy to write a protagonist that blends the best qualities of Anita Blake and Stephanie Plum, but Kim Harrison carries it off with style. This is a fun book! Read it!”<br> — Jim Butcher, #1 <i>New York Times</i> Bestselling Author</b></p><p><b>In the Hollows, the vampires come out to play… and it’s <i>always </i>witching hour.</b></p><p><b>The first book in #1 <i>New York Times</i> bestselling author Kim Harrison’s Hollows series. Read by award-winning narrator Marguerite Gavin!</b></p><p>All the creatures of the night gather in “the Hollows” of Cincinnati, to hide, to prowl, to party . . . and to feed.</p><p>Vampires rule the darkness in a predator-eat-predator world rife with dangers beyond imagining—and it’s Rachel Morgan’s job to keep that world civilized.</p><p>A bounty hunter and a witch with serious sex appeal and an attitude, she’ll bring ’em back alive, dead . . . or undead.</p>"; 
